# 🔥 Brutal Honest Analysis of MovieTracker (Cline-Mastery)

## The Good
- Clean README, well-documented
- Basic Flask patterns are correctly followed (parameterized queries, Jinja2 autoescaping)
- The "hours summary" watchlist with click-to-select is genuinely a nice UX touch
- Consistent Bootstrap 5 theming throughout

---

## 🔴 CRITICAL SECURITY VULNERABILITIES

### 1. `movies.db` IS COMMITTED TO GIT — WITH REAL USER DATA
The database contains a **real email** (`idrissfoka748@gmail.com`) and a **scrypt password hash**. The `.gitignore` only ignores `.env` — no `*.db` rule. This is a **data leak** waiting to happen if the repo goes public or was ever public.

### 2. `debug=True` in Production Mode
```python
# Line 526
app.run(debug=True, host='0.0.0.0', port=5000)
```
Werkzeug debugger = **remote code execution**. Anyone triggering an unhandled exception gets a Python shell in the browser. Catastrophic.

### 3. Hardcoded Fallback Secret Key
```python
app.secret_key = os.environ.get('KEY', 'fallback-secret-key-change-in-production')
```
If `KEY` env var isn't set, everyone gets the same predictable secret. Any session can be forged.

### 4. No CSRF Protection Whatsoever
Every POST form has **zero CSRF tokens**. A malicious site can silently manipulate authenticated users' data.

### 5. No Rate Limiting on Authentication
Login/register endpoints have no rate limiting. Trivial brute force.


## 🟠 MAJOR CODE QUALITY ISSUES

### 7. Fragile Migration System Runs on Every Startup
Lines 428-524: drops/recreates tables based on fragile heuristics. `INSERT INTO ... SELECT ...` then `DROP TABLE` — **data loss risk if interrupted**. Runs on *every* startup instead of being a one-shot migration script.

### 8. No Error Handling Anywhere
Zero `try/except` blocks. DB locked or query fails = ugly Flask error page. App crashes silently.

### 9. `INSERT OR REPLACE` Watchlist Bug
```python
# Line 340
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO watchlist (movie_id, ...) VALUES (...)
```
Triggers on autoincrement `id`, not `movie_id`. Always inserts a new row. Duplicate entries possible for the same movie.

### 10. SQLite Foreign Keys Don't Work Without `PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON`
`ON DELETE CASCADE` is defined but never activated. Deleting a movie orphans its watchlist rows.

### 11. No Server-Side Input Validation
Rating, release_year, duration, episodes, genre — rely solely on HTML attributes. Anything can be POSTed straight into the DB.

### 12. Copy-Pasted JavaScript
`add.html` and `edit.html` have verbatim identical `toggleFields()` functions (~40 lines each).

### 13. Session Never Expires
No `permanent_session_lifetime` set. Cookies missing `httponly`/`secure` flags.

### 14. User Email Displayed in Navbar
`{{ session.user_email }}` visible to shoulder-surfers and screenshots.

### 15. CDN Dependencies Without Integrity Hashes
No `integrity`/`crossorigin` on Bootstrap CDN links. Compromised CDN = arbitrary JS injection.

### 16. Weak Password Policy
Minimum 6 chars, no complexity rules.

### 17. Truncated Flash Message
Line 107: `'Invalid email or pas\n\n'` — visible bug to users.

